@startuml
title Workflow Preview Evaluation (Dry-Run)

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam roundcorner 5

actor "Risk Analyst" as Analyst
participant "UI: Workflow Builder" as UI
participant "Workflow Service" as WF
database "Workflow DB" as WDB
participant "Case Service" as CASE
participant "Warehouse" as WH

== Preview Workflow (Before Publishing) ==
Analyst -> UI: Test workflow impact\n(dry-run mode)
UI -> WF: POST /workflows/{id}/preview\n{case_id OR business_id, sample_size?}
WF -> WDB: SELECT workflow + version + rules
WDB --> WF: workflow data (draft or published)

alt Preview with specific case_id
  WF -> CASE: GET /cases/{case_id}
  CASE --> WF: case data
  
else Preview with business_id (sampling)
  WF -> CASE: GET /cases?business_id={id}&limit={sample_size}
  CASE --> WF: sampled cases[]
end

note right of WF
  Dry-Run Mode:
  • No side effects
  • No persistence
  • No Kafka events
  • Returns "what would happen"
end note

== Evaluation Logic ==
WF -> WF: Evaluate trigger conditions
alt Trigger matches
  WF -> WH: GET /facts/{business_id}
  WH --> WF: facts (kyc, financials, etc.)
  
  loop For each rule (by priority)
    WF -> WF: Evaluate rule conditions\n(against case + facts)
    alt Rule matches (first match wins)
      WF -> WF: Identify matched rule + actions
      note right
        Actions NOT executed
        Just returned for preview
      end note
      break
    end
  end
  
  alt No rule matched
    WF -> WF: Use default_action
  end
else Trigger does not match
  WF -> WF: Skip evaluation
end

== Return Preview Results ==
WF --> UI: 200 OK\n{evaluation_result: {\n  trigger_matched,\n  matched_rule_id?,\n  applied_action[] (preview only),\n  evaluation_log\n}, sampled_cases?}

UI -> UI: Display:\n• Which rule would match\n• Actions that would apply\n• Sample statistics\n• Evaluation logs

note over Analyst, UI
  Analyst can verify workflow logic
  and make adjustments before publishing
end note

note bottom
  **Key Difference from Real Evaluation:**
  
  Preview (Dry-Run):
  ✓ Fetches real data (cases + facts)
  ✓ Evaluates triggers and rules
  ✗ Does NOT execute actions
  ✗ Does NOT persist to workflow_executions
  ✗ Does NOT publish Kafka events
  ✗ Does NOT update case status
  
  Real Evaluation:
  ✓ All of the above PLUS
  ✓ Executes actions (set_field, etc.)
  ✓ Persists execution logs
  ✓ Publishes events and updates cases
end note

@enduml

